@Node INTRODUCTION "UrlManager.guide/Introduction"

@{jcenter}@{u}@{b}Introduction@{ub}@{uu}

@{jleft}I'm writing UrlManager because I want to build an HTTP robot.

An HTTP robot is a program that can automatically download one or more files using HTTP.  Then it can scan those files to search for references to other files that it download upon some conditions and so on...

UrlManager keeps a list of URL in memory.  When started, the only thing it can do is to wait for ARexx commands.

@EndNode

@Node FEATURES "UrlManager.guide/Features"

@{jcenter}@{u}@{b}Features@{ub}@{uu}
@{jleft}@{lindent 4}@{pari -2}
@{par}- Written in C, which means QUICK compared with ARexx scripts
@{par}- Each url is checked to see if already present in the list
@{par}- Each url has a "type" which can be any uppercase character
@{par}- Each url has a "depth" which is a long integer that can be used to indicate how "deep" to search this url for other urls.
@{par}- Many ways to search an url in the list, including AmigaDOS patterns
@{par}- Can read lists of URLs from file
@{par}- Can save an url-list containing all data (depth, type)
@{par}- ...

@{pard}@{lindent 0}

@EndNode

