@Node ARGUMENTS "UrlManager.guide/Arguments"

@{jcenter}@{b}Arguments@{ub}@{uu}

@{jleft}UrlManager can only be used from a Shell.

You can stop it at anytime by sending it CTRL-C.

    @{b}Text arguments@{ub}
    @{" PORT " Link A_PORT}    Name of the ARexx port to open.

@EndNode

@Node A_PORT "UrlManager.guide/Arguments/PORT"

@{b}PORT@{ub}

Required.  Name of the ARexx port to open.  You should use uppercase only if you plan not to always enquote the port-name in your arexx scripts.

@EndNode

@Node TYPES "UrlManager.guide/Types"
@{jcenter}@{b}Types@{ub}@{uu}

@{jleft}A type in UrlManager is a single character which can be any printable character.  (ie letters and numbers)

If it is a letter, the type is uppercased.  This way, in your rexx scripts, 'a' and 'A' are always the same thing.

Examples:

    Q       Queued
    R       Received
    F       Failed

@EndNode

@Node DEPTH "UrlManager.guide/Depth"
@{jcenter}@{b}Depth@{ub}@{uu}

@{jleft}For UrlManager, a depth is simply a signed long integer.

For an url grabber, it can be used to indicate the level of recursion of a single url.  For example a depth >0 could mean "Scan me and download urls contained in me".  All urls contained in this one are added with a depth of 1, and then a depth of 0, which means "don't scan me".

When no depth is specified when adding an url, either with the @{"AddUrl" Link AR_ADDURL} ARexx command or by loading an url list, the depth is set to "-1".

@EndNode

@Node ID "UrlManager.guide/IDs"
@{jcenter}@{b}IDs@{ub}@{uu}

@{jleft}Each url has a unique ID in UrlManager.  This ID is used to get information on a specific url.

@EndNode

@Node AREXX "UrlManager.guide/Using ARexx"
@{jcenter}@{b}Using ARexx with UrlManager@{ub}@{uu}

@{jleft}Each time a command is received, the RC variable and a variable named "UMRES" are both set.

Any command can return at least one of these codes in RC:

    10  Command unknown/mispelled
    15  Error setting secondary result variable (UMRES)

Here's a list of all ARexx commands known of UrlManager:

    @{" ADDURL      " Link AR_ADDURL}
    @{" COUNTTYPE   " Link AR_COUNTTYPE}
    @{" FLUSHALL    " Link AR_FLUSHALL}
    @{" GETDEPTH    " Link AR_GETDEPTH}
    @{" GETHID      " Link AR_GETHID}
    @{" GETINMEM    " Link AR_GETINMEM}
    @{" GETTYPE     " Link AR_GETTYPE}
    @{" GETURL      " Link AR_GETURL}
    @{" KILLPATTERN " Link AR_KILLPATTERN}
    @{" KILLTYPE    " Link AR_KILLTYPE}
    @{" KILLURL     " Link AR_KILLURL}
    @{" LOADFILE    " Link AR_LOADFILE}
    @{" MATCHNAME   " Link AR_MATCHNAME}
    @{" QUIT        " Link AR_QUIT}
    @{" READFILE    " Link AR_READFILE}
    @{" SAVEFILE    " Link AR_SAVEFILE}
    @{" SEARCH      " Link AR_SEARCH}
    @{" SETDEPTH    " Link AR_SETDEPTH}
    @{" SETIOSIZE   " Link AR_SETIOSIZE}
    @{" SETTYPE     " Link AR_SETTYPE}
    @{" SETURL      " Link AR_SETURL}

@EndNode

@Node AR_ADDURL "UrlManager.guide/ARexx/AddUrl"

@{b}AddUrl TYPE/A,URL/A,DEPTH/N@{ub}

AddUrl adds an url to UM's url list.

Arguments:@{lindent 8}@{pari -4}
@{par}TYPE/A:
A single uppercase character representing the @{"type" Link TYPES} of the url.
@{par}URL/A:
The url itself :)
@{par}DEPTH/N:
The @{"depth" Link DEPTH} of the url.  If omitted, -1 is used.
@{pard}@{lindent 0}

RC:
    0   Added.  Url's ID is in UMRES.
    1   The url was already in the list.
    2   Error adding url. (ie not enough memory)
    5   Error parsing args.

UMRES:
    ID of the url.

@EndNode

@Node AR_COUNTTYPE "UrlManager.guide/ARexx/CountType"

@{b}CountType TYPE/A@{ub}

Returns the number of urls of type TYPE.

Arguments:@{lindent 8}@{pari -4}
@{par}TYPE/A:
A single uppercase character representing the @{"type" Link TYPES} of the url.
@{pard}@{lindent 0}

RC:
    0   Ok.  Result in UMRES.
    5   Error parsing args.

UMRES:
    Number of url(s) of the given type.

@EndNode

@Node AR_FLUSHALL "UrlManager.guide/ARexx/FlushAll"

@{b}FlushAll@{ub}

Flush the entire list and reset the @{"IDs" Link ID}.

Arguments:
    None.

RC:
    0   Ok.
   99   Could not create new memory pools.
        You really should issue a @{"Quit" Link AR_QUIT} command
        if you receive this.
UMRES:
    Nothing.

@EndNode

@Node AR_GETDEPTH "UrlManager.guide/ARexx/GetDepth"

@{b}GetDepth ID/A/N@{ub}

Get the depth of an url.

Arguments:@{lindent 8}@{pari -4}
@{par}ID/A/N:
The @{"ID" Link ID} of the url to get depth from.
@{pard}@{lindent 0}

RC:
    0   Depth is in UMRES.
    1   This ID is not in use.
    5   Error parsing args.

UMRES:
    Depth of the url.

@EndNode

@Node AR_GETHID "UrlManager.guide/ARexx/GetHid"

@{b}GetHID@{ub}

Get the highest @{"ID" Link ID} number.

Arguments:
    None.

RC:
    0   Ok.

UMRES:
    Highest @{"ID" Link ID} number.

@EndNode

@Node AR_GETINMEM "UrlManager.guide/ARexx/GetInMem"

@{b}GetInMem@{ub}

Get the total number of URLs in the list.

Arguments:
    None.

RC:
    0   Ok.

UMRES:
    Total number of urls in the list.

@EndNode

@Node AR_GETTYPE "UrlManager.guide/ARexx/GetType"

@{b}GetType ID/A/N@{ub}

Get the type of an url.

Arguments:@{lindent 8}@{pari -4}
@{par}ID/A/N:
The @{"ID" Link ID} of the url to get type from.
@{pard}@{lindent 0}

RC:
    0   Ok.
    1   ID not in use.
    5   Error parsing args.

UMRES:
    The type of the url requested.

@EndNode

@Node AR_GETURL "UrlManager.guide/ARexx/GetUrl"

@{b}GetUrl ID/A/N@{ub}

Get the name of an url.

Arguments:@{lindent 8}@{pari -4}
@{par}ID/A/N:
@{"ID" Link ID} of the url to get name from.
@{pard}@{lindent 0}

RC:
    0   Ok.  Name in UMRES.
    1   ID not in use.
    5   Error parsing args.

UMRES:
    Url.

@EndNode

@Node AR_KILLPATTERN "UrlManager.guide/ARexx/KillPattern"

@{b}KillPattern PATTERN/A@{ub}

Kill all urls matching an AmigaDOS pattern.  (Or an exact url name if no pattern-chars are given :)

Arguments:@{lindent 8}@{pari -4}
@{par}PATTERN/A:
An AmigaDOS pattern.
@{pard}@{lindent 0}

RC:
    0   Ok.
    5   Error parsing args.

UMRES:@{lindent 4}
Quantity of url killed.  0 can either mean that the pattern could not be parsed of that there were no url matching pattern.

@EndNode

@Node AR_KILLTYPE "UrlManager.guide/ARexx/KillType"

@{b}KillType TYPE/A@{ub}

Kill all urls of a specific @{"type" Link TYPES}.

Arguments:@{lindent 8}@{pari -4}
@{par}TYPE/A:
A single uppercase character representing the @{"type" Link TYPES}.
@{pard}@{lindent 0}

RC:
    0   Ok.
    5   Error parsing args.

UMRES:
    Quantity of url killed.

@EndNode

@Node AR_KILLURL "UrlManager.guide/ARexx/KillUrl"

@{b}KillUrl ID/A/N@{ub}

Kill a specific url.

Arguments:@{lindent 8}@{pari -4}
@{par}ID/A/N:
Url @{"ID" Link ID} to kill.
@{pard}@{lindent 0}

RC:
    0   Killed.
    1   ID not in use.
    5   Error parsing args.

UMRES:
    Nothing.

@EndNode

@Node AR_LOADFILE "UrlManager.guide/ARexx/LoadFile"

@{b}LoadFile FILE/A@{ub}

Read a file containing an url list.  One url/line, each line like this:

    <Type> <Depth> <Url>

Only spaces (DEC 32, HEX 20, " ") are allowed between the 3 fields.  (NO tabs...)

Arguments:@{lindent 8}@{pari -4}
@{par}FILE/A:
Filename.
@{pard}@{lindent 0}

RC:
    0   Everything went OK.  QUantity of url added in UMRES.
    1   Error openning/parsing file.
    5   Error parsing args.

UMRES:
    Quantity of url added.

See also:
    @{" SAVEFILE " LINK AR_SAVEFILE}

@EndNode

@Node AR_MATCHNAME "UrlManager.guide/ARexx/MatchName"

@{b}MatchName NAME/A,NOCASE/S@{ub}

Find an url with a specific name.

Arguments:@{lindent 8}@{pari -4}
@{par}NAME/A:
Name of the url.
@{par}NOCASE/S:
If specified, do a case insensitive search.
@{pard}@{lindent 0}

RC:
    0   Ok.  ID in UMRES.
    1   No match.
    5   Error parsing args.

UMRES:
    ID of the url.

@EndNode

@Node AR_QUIT "UrlManager.guide/ARexx/Quit"

@{b}Quit@{ub}

Tells UrlManager to free its memory and to exit.

Arguments:
    None.

RC:
    0   I'm quitting.

UMRES:
    Nothing.

@EndNode

@Node AR_READFILE "UrlManager.guide/ARexx/ReadFile"

@{b}ReadFile FILE/A,TYPE/A,DEPTH/N@{ub}

Read a file containing one url per line.  Each line must only contain the url.

Arguments:@{lindent 8}@{pari -4}
@{par}FILE/A:
The name of the file to read.
@{par}TYPE/A:
The @{"type"} Link TYPES} each url added will have.
@{par}DEPTH/N:
@{"Depth" Link DEPTH} each url will have.  Default: -1.
@{pard}@{lindent 0}

RC:
    0   Ok.  Quantity of url added in UMRES.
    1   Error openning/parsing file.
    5   Error parsing args.

UMRES:
    Quantity of url added.

See also:
    @{" SaveFile " Link AR_SAVEFILE}

@EndNode

@Node AR_SAVEFILE "UrlManager.guide/ARexx/SaveFile"

@{b}SaveFile FILE/A,TYPE/K,PATTERN/K,APPEND/S,FULL/S@{ub}

Selectively save url(s) to disk, either in @{"ReadFile" Link AR_READFILE}'s or @{"LoadFile" Link AR_LOADFILE}'s format.

Arguments:@{lindent 8}@{pari -4}
@{par}FILE/A:
Name of to file to write urls to.
@{par}TYPE/K:
If specified, save only urls of that type.
@{par}PATTERN/K:
If specified, save only urls matching that AmigaDOS pattern.
@{par}APPEND/S:
If specified, append to file instead of overwriting.
@{par}FULL/S:
If present, save a @{"LoadFile" Link AR_LOADFILE} file, if absent, save a @{"ReadFile" Link AR_READFILE} file.
@{pard}@{lindent 0}

RC:
    0   Ok.
    1   Error saving file.
    5   Error parsing args.

UMRES:
    Nothing.

@EndNode

@Node AR_SEARCH "UrlManager.guide/ARexx/Search"

@{b}Search MINID/A/N,PATTERN/K,TYPE/K@{ub}

Search the list (lowest ID first) for an url.

Arguments:@{lindent 8}@{pari -4}
@{par}MINID/A/N
Required.  Lowest ID number to scan.  0 scans all of them..
@{par}PATTERN/K:
AmigaDOS pattenr that must be matched if specified.
@{par}TYPE/K:
If specified, scan only that @{"type" Link TYPES}.
@{pard}@{lindent 0}

RC:
    0   Ok.
    5   Error parsing args.

UMRES:
    ID of the url or 0 if nothing found.

@EndNode

@Node AR_SETDEPTH "UrlManager.guide/ARexx/SetDepth"

@{b}SetDepth ID/A/N,DEPTH/A/N@{ub}

Change the @{"depth" Link DEPTH} of an url.

Arguments:@{lindent 8}@{pari -4}
@{par}ID/A/N:
@{"ID" Link ID} of the url.
@{par}DEPTH/A/N:
New @{"depth" Link DEPTH} of the url.
@{pard}@{lindent 0}

RC:
    0   Ok.
    1   ID not in use.
    5   Error parsing args.

UMRES:
    Nothing.

@EndNode

@Node AR_SETIOSIZE "UrlManager.guide/ARexx/SetIOSize"

@{b}SetIOSize SIZE/A/N@{ub}

Set the size of input/output buffer.

Arguments:@{lindent 8}@{pari -4}
@{par}SIZE/A/N:
Size in bytes.  If < 1024, 1024 is used.  Default: 4096.
@{pard}@{lindent 0}

